Important genes¶

We can test which genes have celltype-specific differential velocity expression, being significantly higher/lower compared to the remaining population. min_corr restricst the test to those with a minimum spearman correlation.

From this discussion maybe worth trying scv.tl.rank_dynamical_genes which orders genes by their likelihood from the dynamical model. See here for some more details.

Phase diagrams - Interpreting the velocities¶

See interpreting velocities for this section for advice. The key seems to be this animation which shows the on (induction) and off (repression) phases. The upper curve is "on" and the lower curve is "off". The line in the middle represents the steady state.

RNA velocity for a particular gene is determined as the residual so how much an observation deviates from the steady-state line. Positive velocity means the gene is up-regulated so more unspliced the spliced compared to the steady state and the converse for down regulated genes.

Kinetic rate parameters by gene¶

See here for more details.

In [15]:
for stage_index, stage_name in enumerate(stage_names):
    adata_for_stage = adata_by_stage[stage_index]
        
    df = adata_for_stage.var
    df = df[(df['fit_likelihood'] > .1) & df['velocity_genes'] == True]

    kwargs = dict(xscale='log', fontsize=16)
    with scv.GridSpec(ncols=3) as pl:
        print(f"Rate parameters for stage={stage_name}")
        pl.hist(df['fit_alpha'], xlabel='transcription rate', **kwargs)
        pl.hist(df['fit_beta'] * df['fit_scaling'], xlabel='splicing rate', xticks=[.1, .4, 1], **kwargs)
        pl.hist(df['fit_gamma'], xlabel='degradation rate', xticks=[.1, .4, 1], **kwargs)

Splicing efficiency¶

See here for discussion of spiking efficieny in erythroid cells.

If we saw spiking effieicny change between cell types we might have an explanation but plots seems to show uniform distribution.

stage= 0
adata_for_stage = adata_by_stage[stage]

counts_s = scv.utils.sum_var(adata_for_stage.layers['spliced'])
counts_u = scv.utils.sum_var(adata_for_stage.layers['unspliced'])
